<div class='introduction f5'>
  <h6 class='ttu tracked'>Changing Input Type</h6>

  <p>So far, we have dealt with a simple text input. What about other forms of
    input?</p>

  <p>We can handle (mostly) everything. Here's a list of supported field types:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>text</li>
    <li>search</li>
    <li>url</li>
    <li>phone</li>
    <li>email</li>
    <li>number</li>
    <li>textarea</li>
  </ul>

  For example, if you want to make the editor a textarea, just pass in
  <code>textarea</code>
  to the
  <code>field</code>
  property.

  <XCard @class='mt2' @type='Code'>
    {{! <CodeSnippet class='code f6' @name='changing-input-type.hbs' /> }}
    {{#let (get-code-snippet 'changing-input-type.hbs') as |snippet|}}
      <CodeBlock
        class='code f6'
        @language={{snippet.language}}
        @code={{snippet.source}}
      />
    {{/let}}
  </XCard>

  <p>
    Here's what that will do.
  </p>

  <XCard @type='Example'>

    <EmberInlineEdit
      class='fl w-50'
      @field='textarea'
      @value={{this.value}}
      @onSave={{fn (mut this.value)}}
    />
  </XCard>
</div>